      </div>
<p>Nioh 3 sees players step into the boots of a fictionalized version of Japan's first shogun, Tokugawa Takechiyo. With supernatural threats on the rise, it's up to Tokugawa to battle these malevolent forces by using <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/nioh-3-dev-shares-how-ninja-gaiden-influenced-the-combat-overhaul/1100-6534898/" data-ref-id="1100-6534898">both samurai and ninja fighting styles</a>. Team Ninja says that its Ninja Gaiden games inspired a shift in the gameplay, and that players can freely shift between these stances.</p><p>The samurai fighting style has a unique Ki Pulse ability that can be used after attacking to recover stamina, while the ninja fighting style has a mist ability that can be used to create a doppelganger of Tokugawa that draws enemy attention away from him.</p><p>Team Ninjaâ€™s next game is <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/ninja-gaiden-4/">Ninja Gaiden 4</a>, launching on 21 October. This new instalment in the cult-classic Ninja Gaiden series has been co-developed with Platinum Games.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
