            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-boss-felt-an-obligation-to-make-a-better-game-after-2042-stumbled/1100-6534972/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/battlefield-6-boss-felt-an-obligation-to-make-a-better-game-after-2042-stumbled.1306671/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6534972">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>It is no secret that Battlefield 2042 had a rough launch, and against that backdrop, DICE boss Rebecka Coutaz said one of her main goals when she joined the company in 2021 was to help make the next Battlefield game, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/battlefield-6-release-date-trailer-news/1100-6526583/" data-ref-id="1100-6526583">Battlefield 6</a>, "one of the best Battlefields the world has ever seen."</p><p>She told <a href="https://www.gamesradar.com/games/battlefield/why-ea-is-razing-battlefield-to-its-foundations-in-order-to-build-something-explosively-new-with-battlefield-6-i-felt-an-obligation-to-create-one-of-the-best-battlefields-the-world-has-ever-seen/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">GamesRadar</a> that she felt an "obligation" to make a better game. "I owe that to the community and to the teams. That is my drive. That's why I'm here," she said.</p>



    
